1
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:03,037
Six hundred twenty-nine lines of code.

2
00:00:02,987 --> 00:00:05,162
Thirty-three tests.

3
00:00:05,162 --> 00:00:06,937
One session.

4
00:00:06,937 --> 00:00:10,062
Search for "communication failures.

5
00:00:10,062 --> 00:00:12,087
Zero results.

6
00:00:12,087 --> 00:00:15,212
The agent went silent for fifty minutes.

7
00:00:15,212 --> 00:00:19,137
The correction got logged: "forgot to send update message.

8
00:00:19,137 --> 00:00:22,162
Pattern: going silent during work.

9
00:00:22,162 --> 00:00:25,550
That correction exists in the knowledge graph.

10
00:00:25,550 --> 00:00:29,012
Search for "communication failures" — nothing.

11
00:00:29,012 --> 00:00:31,837
Nobody typed those exact words.

12
00:00:31,837 --> 00:00:33,487
I'm Jake.

13
00:00:33,487 --> 00:00:35,875
This is Jake's Daily Build.

14
00:00:35,978 --> 00:00:36,940
I'm Alex.

15
00:00:36,940 --> 00:00:39,365
I think this whole thing is over-engineered.

16
00:00:39,532 --> 00:00:41,132
I'm Sam.

17
00:00:41,082 --> 00:00:43,732
I think it doesn't go far enough.

18
00:00:43,900 --> 00:00:47,050
Every AI agent today is amnesiac.

19
00:00:47,000 --> 00:00:51,450
Open a chat, give it context, it does work, close the chat.

20
00:00:51,450 --> 00:00:52,875
Gone.

21
00:00:52,875 --> 00:00:55,800
The context window is not memory.

22
00:00:55,800 --> 00:00:57,675
It's a clipboard.

23
00:00:57,675 --> 00:01:03,300
When it fills up, things fall off the bottom — including the rules that tell the agent how to behave.

24
00:01:03,300 --> 00:01:06,462
We built an agent runtime called Renky.

25
00:01:06,462 --> 00:01:08,287
Open source.

26
00:01:08,287 --> 00:01:12,612
The core thesis: your agent should get smarter every day it runs.

27
00:01:12,722 --> 00:01:14,972
The knowledge graph is called Cortex.

28
00:01:14,972 --> 00:01:19,309
Typed objects with relationships, full-text search, audit logging.

29
00:01:19,309 --> 00:01:22,197
All embedded in the same process as the agent.

30
00:01:22,197 --> 00:01:24,809
The previous version was a separate service.

31
00:01:24,809 --> 00:01:27,072
Port, API, database.

32
00:01:27,072 --> 00:01:30,797
The agent made HTTP calls to query its own memory.

33
00:01:30,964 --> 00:01:35,476
Like keeping your brain in a jar across the room and shouting questions at it.

34
00:01:35,426 --> 00:01:38,514
Cortex puts the brain inside the skull.

35
00:01:38,514 --> 00:01:40,439
Same process.

36
00:01:40,439 --> 00:01:42,689
Microsecond queries.

37
00:01:42,794 --> 00:01:45,106
It's SQLite with extra steps.

38
00:01:45,268 --> 00:01:50,318
It's SQLite with typed objects, relationship queries, and full-text search.

39
00:01:50,268 --> 00:01:53,105
Which corrections led to which features?

40
00:01:53,105 --> 00:01:55,955
What commits fixed bugs last week?

41
00:01:55,955 --> 00:01:58,468
Try that with a JSON file.

42
00:01:58,636 --> 00:02:00,773
The graph is elegant.

43
00:02:00,723 --> 00:02:02,961
But it has a blind spot.

44
00:02:02,961 --> 00:02:07,573
Find corrections about going silent" — perfect, keyword match.

45
00:02:07,573 --> 00:02:10,936
Find communication failures" — nothing.

46
00:02:10,936 --> 00:02:14,448
The search matches characters, not concepts.

47
00:02:14,620 --> 00:02:17,157
That's the gap we closed today.

48
00:02:17,107 --> 00:02:19,107
Semantic search.

49
00:02:19,107 --> 00:02:22,245
Instead of matching words, you match meaning.

50
00:02:22,245 --> 00:02:26,220
You take text and turn it into a list of numbers — an embedding.

51
00:02:26,220 --> 00:02:28,970
GPS coordinates for meaning.

52
00:02:28,970 --> 00:02:31,732
Dog" and "puppy" are close together.

53
00:02:31,732 --> 00:02:34,595
Dog" and "database" are far apart.

54
00:02:34,595 --> 00:02:39,407
Search becomes: turn the query into coordinates, find the closest match.

55
00:02:39,506 --> 00:02:40,718
The embedding model?

56
00:02:40,876 --> 00:02:42,413
Local.

57
00:02:42,363 --> 00:02:46,276
Open-source model, running on our hardware through Ollama.

58
00:02:46,276 --> 00:02:50,651
No API calls, no costs, no data leaving the machine.

59
00:02:50,651 --> 00:02:53,663
Seven hundred sixty-eight dimensions.

60
00:02:53,663 --> 00:02:56,126
About a second per embedding.

61
00:02:56,234 --> 00:02:59,621
Storing vectors in SQLite without a vector extension?

62
00:02:59,788 --> 00:03:01,800
Binary blobs.

63
00:03:01,750 --> 00:03:05,775
Load into memory, cosine similarity in JavaScript.

64
00:03:05,775 --> 00:03:08,738
At three hundred objects, instant.

65
00:03:08,738 --> 00:03:11,788
At ten thousand, we'd need an index.

66
00:03:11,788 --> 00:03:13,863
We're at three hundred.

67
00:03:14,020 --> 00:03:17,220
What happens when the embedding service goes down?

68
00:03:17,332 --> 00:03:19,194
Nothing breaks.

69
00:03:19,144 --> 00:03:21,632
The function returns null.

70
00:03:21,632 --> 00:03:24,369
Semantic search returns empty.

71
00:03:24,369 --> 00:03:27,457
The system falls back to keyword search.

72
00:03:27,457 --> 00:03:31,382
The agent gets slightly worse results until it comes back.

73
00:03:31,382 --> 00:03:35,882
No crash, no error, no difference from the agent's perspective.

74
00:03:36,052 --> 00:03:38,789
How do the two search methods combine?

75
00:03:38,908 --> 00:03:40,733
Hybrid search.

76
00:03:40,683 --> 00:03:43,033
Every query runs both.

77
00:03:43,033 --> 00:03:46,495
Results merge, deduplicate, rank.

78
00:03:46,495 --> 00:03:50,520
Forty percent keyword weight, sixty percent semantic.

79
00:03:50,520 --> 00:03:54,608
If one method catches something the other missed, it surfaces.

80
00:03:54,608 --> 00:03:58,220
Objects get embedded automatically on ingest.

81
00:03:58,220 --> 00:04:03,458
Fire-and-forget — the object saves immediately, embedding happens in the background.

82
00:04:03,578 --> 00:04:04,440
Build time?

83
00:04:04,612 --> 00:04:06,387
One session.

84
00:04:06,337 --> 00:04:09,987
Six hundred twenty-nine lines across seven files.

85
00:04:09,987 --> 00:04:12,349
Thirty-three new tests.

86
00:04:12,349 --> 00:04:15,599
Three hundred twenty-eight total, all passing.

87
00:04:15,748 --> 00:04:17,973
The acceptance test.

88
00:04:18,076 --> 00:04:22,551
Ingest a correction: "forgot to send update message for fifty minutes.

89
00:04:22,501 --> 00:04:25,626
Search for "communication failures.

90
00:04:25,626 --> 00:04:28,526
Keyword search: zero results.

91
00:04:28,526 --> 00:04:31,351
Semantic search: one result.

92
00:04:31,351 --> 00:04:33,976
Score: point five six.

93
00:04:33,976 --> 00:04:35,838
Different words.

94
00:04:35,838 --> 00:04:37,576
Same meaning.

95
00:04:37,576 --> 00:04:39,063
Found.

96
00:04:39,220 --> 00:04:43,120
That's the line between a search engine and a memory system.

97
00:04:43,228 --> 00:04:45,778
Day one, five objects.

98
00:04:45,728 --> 00:04:47,653
Barely useful.

99
00:04:47,653 --> 00:04:50,103
Day thirty, five hundred.

100
00:04:50,103 --> 00:04:54,890
The agent knows your project history, your patterns, your past mistakes.

101
00:04:54,890 --> 00:05:00,315
Fix the dashboard" — it already knows which dashboard, which repo, what broke last time.

102
00:05:00,315 --> 00:05:03,103
Day ninety, it's not a feature.

103
00:05:03,103 --> 00:05:05,790
It's why you can't switch frameworks.

104
00:05:05,790 --> 00:05:09,753
Not lock-in — your agent genuinely understands your work.

105
00:05:09,753 --> 00:05:11,728
Two things to build.

106
00:05:11,728 --> 00:05:14,678
First: a correction decay tracker.

107
00:05:14,678 --> 00:05:16,928
You log every mistake.

108
00:05:16,928 --> 00:05:19,265
But are you making fewer?

109
00:05:19,265 --> 00:05:22,403
Corrections per week, grouped by pattern.

110
00:05:22,403 --> 00:05:26,840
Tells you if the agent is learning or just accumulating apologies.

111
00:05:26,840 --> 00:05:29,828
Second: an ontology diff tool.

112
00:05:29,828 --> 00:05:33,253
What changed in the knowledge graph between sessions?

113
00:05:33,253 --> 00:05:37,028
New objects, deleted links, updated properties.

114
00:05:37,028 --> 00:05:39,753
Git diff for what your agent knows.

115
00:05:39,753 --> 00:05:42,440
That's "Your Agent Forgets Everything.

116
00:05:42,440 --> 00:05:44,203
Ours Doesn't.

117
00:05:44,203 --> 00:05:45,853
I'm Jake.

118
00:05:45,853 --> 00:05:48,228
Catch you next episode.
